subject:

THE CALL TO CONSTANCY (read Mt. 23:23-32)
===================================================================
verse:

“You have neglected the more important matters of the
law—justice, mercy and faithfulness. . . .you strain out a
gnat but swallow a camel.” (Mt. 23:23-24)

===================================================================
reflection:

Jesus, by precept and example, encourages constancy in one’s
Christian faith and love. In His Sermon on the Mount, He
tried to correct religious imbalance, such as this
inconsistency: “You have heard that it was said, ‘Love your
neighbor and hate your enemy.’ But I tell you: Love your
enemies and pray for those who persecute you” (Mt. 5:43-44).
Jesus helped us to be consistent by setting this priority:
Seek first His kingdom and His righteousness, and all these
things will be given to you as well” (Mt. 6:33).

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord Jesus, help me to love without hesitation, even when it
feels difficult. Teach my heart to be steadfast in faith and
gentle in spirit. May I seek Your kingdom in all that I do,
trusting that You alone provide what I truly need. Let my
life reflect Your constant love today and always. Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
